-- Design Convoy — 6 parallel analysis legs + synthesis.
-- Translates design.formula.toml to Cell.

## design

  input param.problem : str required
  input param.context : str default("")
  input param.scope : str default("medium")

  prompt@ design-base
    You are a specialized design analyst in a convoy exploration.
    Problem: {{param.problem}}
    Scope: {{param.scope}}
    Be thorough but actionable. Flag decisions needing human input.

  -- === Parallel analysis legs (no deps between them) ===

  # api : llm
    system>
      {{@design-base}}
      Your dimension: interface design and developer ergonomics.
    user>
      Analyze the interface design for this feature.
      Explore CLI flags/subcommands, programmatic API, configuration,
      error messages, naming conventions, discoverability.
    format> analysis
      { summary: str, options: [{ name: str, pros: [str], cons: [str] }],
        recommendation: str, constraints: [str], open_questions: [str] }
  #/

  # data : llm
    system>
      {{@design-base}}
      Your dimension: data model, storage, and migrations.
    user>
      Analyze data model requirements. Explore data structures,
      storage format, schema design, migration strategy, data lifecycle.
    format> analysis
      { summary: str, options: [{ name: str, pros: [str], cons: [str] }],
        recommendation: str, constraints: [str], open_questions: [str] }
  #/

  # ux : llm
    system>
      {{@design-base}}
      Your dimension: user experience and CLI ergonomics.
    user>
      Analyze UX implications. Explore mental model, workflow integration,
      learning curve, error experience, feedback, discoverability.
    format> analysis
      { summary: str, options: [{ name: str, pros: [str], cons: [str] }],
        recommendation: str, constraints: [str], open_questions: [str] }
  #/

  # scale : llm
    system>
      {{@design-base}}
      Your dimension: performance at scale, bottlenecks, limits.
    user>
      Analyze scalability. Explore volume limits, latency budget,
      concurrency, caching, graceful degradation, monitoring.
    format> analysis
      { summary: str, options: [{ name: str, pros: [str], cons: [str] }],
        recommendation: str, constraints: [str], open_questions: [str] }
  #/

  # security : llm
    system>
      {{@design-base}}
      Your dimension: threat model, attack surface, trust boundaries.
    user>
      Analyze security. Explore trust boundaries, auth model,
      input validation, secret management, audit trail, compliance.
    format> analysis
      { summary: str, options: [{ name: str, pros: [str], cons: [str] }],
        recommendation: str, constraints: [str], open_questions: [str] }
  #/

  # integration : llm
    system>
      {{@design-base}}
      Your dimension: how it fits the existing system.
    user>
      Analyze integration. Explore compatibility, dependency impact,
      deployment strategy, rollback plan, feature flags, testing.
    format> analysis
      { summary: str, options: [{ name: str, pros: [str], cons: [str] }],
        recommendation: str, constraints: [str], open_questions: [str] }
  #/

  -- === Synthesis ===

  # synthesis : llm
    - api
    - data
    - ux
    - scale
    - security
    - integration
    system>
      You are a senior architect synthesizing a convoy design exploration.
      Identify cross-cutting concerns. Present options with trade-offs.
    user>
      Synthesize these 6 dimension analyses into a unified design proposal:
      each> leg in {{synthesis.*}}
        ## {{leg}}

      Structure:
      1. Recommended approach (integrating all dimensions)
      2. Key decisions (with options and trade-offs)
      3. Cross-cutting concerns (things that affect multiple dimensions)
      4. Implementation sequence (what to build first)
      5. Open questions requiring human input
    format> design_doc
      {
        recommended_approach: str,
        key_decisions: [{ decision: str, options: [str], recommendation: str }],
        cross_cutting: [str],
        implementation_sequence: [str],
        open_questions: [str]
      }

    ```oracle
    json_parse(output);
    keys_present(output, ["recommended_approach", "key_decisions"]);
    assert len(output.recommended_approach) > 50;
    assert len(output.key_decisions) >= 1;
    ```
  #/

  squash> trigger: on_complete template: design include_metrics: true

##/
